  "text": "In sum, our data are consistent with a mechanism of feature-based attention that influences not only earlier and intermediate, but also more complex non-spatial representations of visual input perhaps similar to the featurespecific object shape representations that are observed in monkey IT [CITATION_1] . From these areas, activity might cascade back to earlier cortical and subcortical areas. This would be in good agreement with imaging studies that found evidence for entire networks of brain areas being associated with attention to shapes [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
